Gunmen suspected to be Boko Haram insurgents attacked motorists at Lantaiwa Village of Tarmuwa local government area of Yobe State. Witnesses said the insurgents attacked the travellers at about 3:00 pm, yesterday, shooting sporadically. According to a witness, the insurgents were sighted moving around Lantawa Village about an hour before they stormed the highway. Many travellers, drivers of buses scampered into the bush for safety, amidst the confusion. One of the travellers who did not want his name mentioned on print confirmed that, many travellers were attacked and some others kidnapped on Lantaiwa Village on Friday. Another witness, a driver that escaped from the attack, told our correspondent that the suspected Boko Haram targeted travellers from the state capital going to Tarmuwa, Dapchi, Gashua and Gaidam local government areas of the state. Responding to the development, the Acting Assistant Director of the Army Public Relations, Sector 2 Operation Lafiya Dole, Lieutenant Chinonso Oteh, has confirmed the incident, saying that suspected members of Boko Haram have been attacking travellers near Lantaiwa Village in Tarmuwa local government area of Yobe State.